title: The one i called friend.....
author: rose
text: remember when i cuddled in your arms.  the bitter cold nights we went through.  the nights with snow, rain, and hail.   remember our first date.  the candelabrum candle,  the dark sky,  a frozen lake to skate on.   remember our first kiss.  against a tree,   at 12:oo am the brisk wind blowing in my raven colored hair.   remember our first adventure.  traveled to rome, romania, and italy.  the scary stories,  the new scenery,  the towering buildings.   remember the our first argument.  about the in laws. lol.  but soon got resolved.   remember the big move.  you left for a year.  my lonely nights,  my dreaded life.   remember the big come back.  the night of optimism.  when you kissed me and i melted in your arms.  when you said i'll never leave again.   remember our last words.  it was all a big set up.  for that i hate you.  you never loved me,  you and your brother just wanted to hurt me.  for that i you.  you never said sorry,  even if you did you wouldn't mean i.  for that i hate.  remember when you said you loved me,  why did you lie?  alexander, i thought i called you friend. .

title: I Remember Sunshine
author: ryan
text: i remember sunshine,  flowers,  love,  and friends.  days when morning time never seemed to end.  times when love was new,  when i first thought of you i remember sunshine do you remember too?  minds were astray morning gave in to day smiles were fought over for so many always frowned.  love was only a word.  no longer a deep emotion.  hearts went down with submarines,  deep inside the ocean.   i remember sunshine it seems like only days ago when i first saw it i remember sunshine but now it's destroyed by rain.  i remember sunshine but who brought on this pain? i remember sunshine but somehow it is gone who remembers sunshine? those who live in yesterday who choose to never live today.   i remember everything as if it happened today instead of the day before when it is begun and no one remembers anymore.  i remember,  but really i shouldn't i need to say goodbye,   because tomorrow is just another day,  another word for me to say.

title: Maybe I'm Lost

title: A Poem About Rain
author: sabrina
text: quietly i hear the dripping rain,  slowly sliding down my window pane.  just like the water in my drain,  quietly i hear the dripping rain.   quietly i hear the dripping rain,  slowly it begins to stop.  i stuck my head out,  to see if it had stopped.   but when i did,  on my forehead i felt a drop!  the rain started up again,  but this time, even bigger drops.  this time hopefully,  it will never stop!

title: Why Everybody Calls Me Klutzarilla
author: sade
text: it is raining i slip and i fell in mud.  my clothes was really muddy.  and i had to school.  everyone laugh.  in lunch i spilled my milk and i slip on my milk and got it  all on the back of my new pants.  in the hallway my shoes were untied and i fell on my pretty face.  on the way home it was still raining  iwas trying to walk down the hill  when i trip on a huge stick and i went tumbling down the wet muddy hill.  and i came home coverd with muddy clothes.  that is why everybody calls me klutzarilla.

title: A Cranberry Dream
author: sade
text: the night before thanksgiving as i lay in my bed,  visions of rich and red cranberries dance in my head.  i was having a nightmare, or was it a dream.  it was the night before thanksgiving,   i wanted to scream.  as i ran to the store to get six  cans more of the cranberries i adore,  but when i got there the door was locked,  and i had ran a couple of blocks,  sad and upset,  head in my hand.   i said to myself this just bad plan.  but just then i heard,  the ticking of a clock,  tick,  tick, tick,  tock,  ring,  as i jumped from my bed,  the clock was  telling me,  it is now thanksgiving it was just a cranberry sauce dream.

title: The Different Shape And Size Of Clocks
author: sade
text: i am on my way to buy a clock down the street and across the block,  once inside the clock store i see clocks that are hanging on a tree.  i see animal clocks,  big clocks,  and lots of different square clocks, .  clocks all over everywhere as i am walking through i see,  kitchen clocks,  bedroom clocks ,  happy face clocks,  and clocks with locks.  clocks shaped like books ,  pretty clocks that make you look.  why,  oh! why so many clocks? all them ring and go tick tock.  look at the bird inside that clock,  tick,  tick,  tick,  i love clocks.

title: Different Kinds Of Size And Skin
author: sade
text: people come in different skin,  sizes, sizes and cultures you can learn from everyone you meet culture , sizes, and skin if you judging people you can't win. try putting yourself inside their rim can you see that it just shoudn't matter to you and me we are are on the planet tat is free. all this culture , skin and size does it really matter? we have lots of different trees. they all get along so why can't we?

title: When You Are Fighting With A Friend
author: sade
text: when you are fighting with a friend both must realize no one wins.  saying things you can't take back takes your friendship off the track take the time to talk it out one on one time wiyhout a shout both must think think about here's question's you should ask each other   was the argurment worth losing a friend?  both must say sorry,  can we start again?   aguments are never worth losing a good is it?  one that's their for you to the end.   think of the how and why of this poem when you argue with your friend.

title: Why?
author: sade
text: there are lots of things to ask in the world such as. . . .   why is the sky blue? why do guneia pigs squeeks? why do cows moo? why is the grass green? why do birds yell? why does the snow fall? why do dogs bark? why do cheetahs think we are enemies? why does it rain? why is it always hot?   see there are lots and lots of questions in the world to be ask and some that people can't answer not even the goverment oh yeah and one more question why do the goverment can't answer any of these questions? why? do you know why?

title: Chores
author: sade
text: chores chores how exhausting these are the chores that make it more exhausting such as. . . . . .  clean your your room,  wash dishes,  sweep the floor,  mop the floor,  clean out your animals cages(if you have some animals) take out the stinky trash,   wash your clothes,    there area few chores you have to do besides clean your room , take out the trash, and wash clothes because you should always do that but they still are chores that you have to do and also you got homework to do and how are you going to do all of that and then you have to get up for school without no sleep  see all of those things makes it more diffucult that is why parents always tell the kids to do their chores,

title: Discovering Treasure
author: sade
text: it will be wonderful the treasure will be so bright i will lose my eye sight .   but i will not take the treasure that will be wrong i will just look at it. it is so bright it makes the sun go out of light it's so cool it makes me drool. maybe when it is not so hot i will come back when it cools down i never thought treasure will be so fun to look at and discover.

title: Animals Are So Important To Me
author: sade
text: animals are very very important to me even if i don't know where it have been it they are still important to me.   there are 2 animals that i have saved  there was one cat who always came to my house and sat on my porch and he looked very hungry.  so i took my money out of my allowence,  and buyed it some cat food and even though it belonged to somebody it looked like the owner wasn't taken care of the cat very much.  everytime the cat didn't come i just wanted fo the cat to come back.  i always fed it because that was only reason why the cat came to my door just to eat some food. but i think the owner should have took care of the cat better. last but not least one more animal story one day i was hanging my clothes on the clothes line and i saw this bird flew into this hole with a huge rock over top of it.  the bird could not get out the rock was to heavy for the bird to lift it out,  so i pick up the rock it was also kind of hard for me to get it up off of the bird , but i manage to pick the rock off of the bird and the bird flew away. it looked like the bird's arm was injured but it still could of fly.   even though cats or birds may have fleas but you should take the time to help them.  cause i have 6 animals in my house and if i see something wrong  with them i take the time to help them even outside animals and so should you.  that is why animals is very very important to me.

title: Purple Is The Color For Me
author: sade
text: purple is the color for me,  if i had my way i would have purple trees,  when i look up into the sky and see no purple stars i wonder why?   soda,  socks,  and sheets are fine as long as they are purple and are mine.   crayons,  markers,  purple balls,  i'm not finished that's not all.     in my bathroom i love to run,  purple shower curtains hung for fun.  in my shower on a rope is my very purple soap.   and in my bedroom upon my bed is my purple bedspread and pillow were i lay my head.   this is all the purple i will do,  because if it is not purple i am blue.

title: ThunderStorms
author: sade
text: grey,  dark clouds,  lighting,  rain.  here it comes it's a pain.  flashing lighting rule the sky,  burning lightning flashing by,  lights go out,  powers gone!.  refrigerator off,  powers gone!! no computer, powers gone!!! no t. v.  powers gone!!!!,  no music powers gone!!!!! this the power of a thunderstorm,  i will be glad when it is gone.

title: All My Friends
author: sade
text: i have friends yes i do,  i've had friends since i was two.  i have smart friends and help me with my homework.  i have clumsy friends also party friends,  i have book club friends i eat my lunch with ,  i have chitty chatty friends when i am sad or mad.     i have plenty of friends of having friends they will always be there for me. i just love my friends.

title: It's The Beat''
author: sade
text: that makes me pat my feet.  i love to dance to that lean to it rock with it beat.  i love all the dance videos i love the dances crazy clothes.  i like to pretend i am singing with a mic i'm glad they can't hear me that wouldn't be tight.   this is all to the beat the next time you dance think it's the beat!!!

title: Hair,Hair,Everywhere
author: sade
text: there are lots of hair everywhere.  hair on your head,  hair on your legs,  hair on your arms,  hair on bears,  hair on your eyebrows,  hair on monkeys,  hair on rabits,  hair on ferrects, and hair on guniea pigs.   if you think that's lots of hair.  i'm on my way and i am set,  to go to the zoo to see the marosets.

title: A Hot Day Dream!!!
author: sade
text: today was a hot day to bad whe had to go to school.  i love school but not on a hot day in classi was begging for water it was so hot in my class i could not even think in my math class. we all needed a pool afther school we stayed inside the office but we were making to much noise.  i felt like a fool for talking loud but i needed to be cool. so we had to stand outside which made me hotter. but when i got home i was happy to have air but bad luck the air conditner broke down and i thought i was going to die. but when i woke up it was a dream and i woke up in cold frezzing air that was one hot day dream!!!

title: I love Breakfast
author: sade
text: i love breakfast what i like to eat is cereal ,  pancakes and waffles.  the best thing about breakfast you can eat and sit in front of the t. v.   and watch your favorite shows but sometimes i just eat plan cereal but that is still breakfast but another thing that i like about breakfast is that eating it on saturdays because you can just take your time instead of rushing but i just love it.

title: Snowy Days
author: sade
text: what a beatiful snowy day,  the best part is no school!!! you just sit around play snowball fight with your friends how awesome is that? you can watch t. v.  drink nice hot chocolate.  snowy days are for children that wants to have fun,  it's for children who needs to relax,   it's good you won't have to hear the bells ring to change to different classes all day, just peace and quiet  the only part on snowy days that i hate are snowy days don't last long,  because when the snow melts it's back to school.  school is fun but reading the same thing over again is still not fun!!!  once again you will have to hear the bell ring to change to different classes!!!!

title: The Worst Day Ever!!!!!
author: sade
text: today was starting out wonderful but when i got to school it was getting kind of bad when i went to school my teacher was looking for our assement when i made a mistake and i left it at home and my teacher didn't believe me she thought i was making up a story and i had terrible grade on that assement then in lunch i left my lunch money at home and i starved and i did not eat till i got home. in gym we were playing soccor 5 to tied we were tied and all we had to do was make one more shot and we won but i scored in my own goal and they one and everybody was mad at me. then i miss my bus.  and i had a vollyball game and we lost 3 to 5. andf one more thing my friend let me borrow her lucking bracellet and i broked it and i had to by her a new one.   see how bad my day went it was not bad it was out of controll!!! that was my worst day ever.

title: My Love Of Cats
author: sade

title: I Hate Rainy Days
author: sade
text: bad luck ,  bad luck  today was a rainy day and i hate rainy days.  because i think  rainy days will get you bad luck.  well let me start you off with on my way to school.  i was walking to school with my friends and i had to carry my stuff in my hand because my bookbag broke.  then this big bus came and ran through the mud and i got mud all on my neww pants.  my homework fell out of my notebook and   fell in the discusting mud.  then i step in dog poop.   i came in the class smelling like a ferret cage that has never been clean out for days.  in lunch we had meatballs and i trip and fell and got chocalate milk all over my shirt and meatballs all over my shoes and socks i could not get another lunch because i pay for lunch.  afther school it stop raining but as soon as i got outside and started walking it started to rain again.  and my hair was soke and wet and so was my clothes.  when i got home my mother made me take a 2 hour shower.   i told you that rainy days is bad luck oh how i hate rainy days.

title: The Worst Day Ever!!!!!

text: today was starting out wonderful ,  but when i got school my day was getting kind of bad,  i went to my classroom my teacher was loooking for her assignments she given us for homework last night,  that's when i realize that i made a mistake and left my homework at home,  my teacher was kind of mad my teacher did not believe me she thought i maded it up,  i got a terrible grade on my assignments. then in lunch i left my lunch money at home i thought that i would starve that day . in gym we were play in soccer we were tied 5to5 all we had to do was make one more shot and we will win ewe lost by 1 point because i kicked the ball in over own net everybody was mad at me. then i miss my bus i had a volleyball game and we lost 3to5. one more thing my friend let me borrow her lucky bracelet i broked it i had to buy her a new one.  see how bad my day went it was out of control!!!!!that was my worst day ever.

title: It Takes A Village
author: sade
text: it takes a village,  do you hear what i say? it takes a village to raise kids these ole days.   when i'm runing late for school,   my granny doesn't play,  she wakes me up in her own granny way,  and as she fixes my breakfast i hear her say it takes a village do you hear what i say? it takes a village to raise kids these ole days.   street lights coming on and us kids just want to play, all the kids are sad cause it's the middle of our game.  but up and down the street parents are calling our names,  as i head for home,  i hear the parents say it takes a village do you hear what i say? it takes a village to raise kids these ole days.   sleeping late on saturdays,  my granny aint having that! got to help my neighbors walk the dog and brush the cat,  help carry groceries,  and help mowing grass,  teaching responsibity,  learning how to stretch a dollar,  and work without getting paid.   cause the elders teach us that,  getting paid is not always the way,  learning to help others is what we are suppose to do,  so as i do my saturday chores i hear the elders say,  it takes a village,  do you hear what i say? it takes a village to raise kids these ole days.   to make me a better person so that i will be able to stand and as i am growing up i can see the village plan.  it does take a village it does take a plan  it does take my granny and the village has her hand.

title: My Favorite Book
author: sagarika
text: my favorite book is about witches and wizards,  turning rats into cockroaches and making potions out of lizards.  ''harry potter'' is its name,   a wonderful book that has achieved great fame and acclaim.   j. k.  rowling is the author,  oh,  how brilliant is she!! she is well-known as the ''queen of fantasy''.  the book is as exciting as it can be,   once i start to read it,  it becomes a part of me!!  the stories are so funny that you laugh until you cry,  in school they teach you how to cast some spells and on broomsticks how to fly! for supper everyone enjoys,  pumpkin juice and pumpkin pie,  and while the suppers' going on some ghosts come floating by.   children choose their house by wearing a ''sorting'' hat,  end up joining ''gryffindor'',  ''ravenclaw'',  ''hufflepuff'' or   ''slytherin'' - just like that.  they play ''quidditch'' flying on broomsticks in the field,  and often end up fighting one another till someone does yield.   they take classes such as ''spells'',  ''potions'' and ''transfiguration'',  ''history of magic'' is where they learn about their 'magical federation'.  some of the teachers are professors snape,  mcgonagall and sprout,  professor sprout teaches ''herbology' with plants that make the students scream and shout.                                           but all wizards in the book are not good and kind,  plenty of evil ones are there,  that you will find.  for one evil wizard killing was just a game,  and lord voldemort was that wizard's name.   harry potter's parents were killed by voldemort when he was small and tiny,  but he survived,  went to hogwarts and had two friends called ron and hermione.  they forged a friendship that was so good and strong,  that it did not go amiss even when something went wrong.   albus dumbledore,  the headmaster was a powerful wizard,  he could make a storm of fire or a very cold blizzard.  he was the only person voldemort ever feared,  and he became uneasy whenever dumbledore appeared.   the fights they have,  the spells they cast,  they all make my heart beat oh so fast! the plot,  the thrill and,  oh,  the story-line,  is just extremely exciting and perfectly divine.   it's a book that's so good that you'll read it with glee,  i know it'll cast a spell on you too,  as it did on me!!

title: The Magic Of Knowledge
author: samantha
text: the magic of knowledge is all around,  in the air,  and in the ground.   it's the wind blowing the trees,  it's the flowers for the bees.  it's from anyone you meet,  from a friend or person on the street.   the magic of knowledge is in the store,  in the car,  behind the door.   it's the cat's curiosity,  it's the owl's philosiphy.  it's the fish's will to swim,  it's the child's goal to sucseed in gym.   the magic of knowledge is at your door,  it's your key to unlocking life's secrets.  now,  go!  explore!

title: Family of Six
author: sarah
text: i live in a family of six and it makes my life very busy.  there are always distractions and they make me dizzy.   i go to my room to be all alone,  laying on my bed,  when suddenly my sister comes in yelling that my brother is dead.   at first i don't listen,  thinking its all a lie,  when my mom comes in screaming,  ''your brother did die!''  i run upstairs to see him on the floor.  my heart jumps with pain and i run out the door.   how could this be? was it all really true? now i sat crying,  feeling the deepest blue.   one year later i walked to his grave.  maybe if i hadn't been napping,  he could have been saved.   now my family of six,  has gone down to five,  because my innocent brother is now not alive.

title: School/Friends
author: sarah
text: school/ friends ~somewhere between the procrastination . . . and the homework . . . and the incessant forwards . . . and the friendships . . . and the nasty cafeteria food . . . and the calls to each other complaining about crushes ~somewhere between the phone calls to old friends . . . and the ''i miss you's'' . . . and the ''i love you's'' . . . and the ''what are we doing tonight's'' . . . and somewhere between all of the changing & growing. .  ~somewhere between the classes . . . and the skipping classes . . . and the studying for tests . . . and the pretending to study for tests . . . and the downright not studying for tests. . .  ~i forgot.  . . . i forgot what high school is all about.  . . . i forgot what it meant to cry . . . i forgot that pretending to be happy doesn't make you happy.  . . . and that pretending to be smart doesn't make you smart.  . . . i forgot that you can't just forget the past in fear of the future.  . . . i forgot that you can't control falling in love . . . and that you can't make yourself fall in love.  ~i learned that i can love.  . . . i learned that it's okay to mess up . . . and it's okay to ask for help . . . and it's okay to feel like crap.  . . . i learned its okay to complain and whine to all your friends for a whole day.  . . . i learned that sometimes the things you want most you just can't have.  . . . i learned that the greatest thing about high school isnt the parties or the drinking or the hook-ups. . .  . . . it's the friendships which means taking chances.  . . . i learned that sometimes the things we want to forget are the things which we most need to talk about.  . . . i learned that letters from friends are the most important thing . . . and that sending cards to your friends makes you feel better.  ~but,  basically,  i just learned that my friends . . . both old and new . . . are the most important people to me in the world . . . and without them,  i wouldn't be who i am today

title: Michelle
author: sarah
text: so young,  so alive.  there was happiness in her eyes  she was here til' the e. m. s would say that she wouldn't see another day.   she was great at everything,  but who knew what the day would bring.   michelle is gone but we are here.  everyone shed more than one tear.   nineteen years is such a short time,  first year of college,  the only thing on her mind.   a car crash ended her life,  and a pain cut through us like a knife.   i have one last thing to say to you,             goodbye michelle.

title: A Game of Hockey
author: seth
text: the fans arrive to see a game of hockey.  they take their seats,  as the two teams  go out onto the ice.  the puck is soundlessly dropped,  and the game begins.   there is a blur of colors as the players begin to skate  up and down the ice as fast as light.  the puck is dumped into the opposing teamâ’s zone.  the opposition soon gathers the puck,   and begins to skate  out of their zone.   our team skates at them like a train,   refusing to stop.  they take the puck from the statue of a player and enter the zone.   a triangle is formed and the puck bounces  off one stick blade only to collide with another.   it then reaches the pointman,  who launches it.  the puck screams in pain because of how hard it was struck by the mixture  of fiberglass and tape.   suddenly,   all goes into slow motion.  the puck,  flying through the air faster than the players can skate,  seems to be traveling as slow as a snail.  it inches its way toward the net,  and grazes the goalieâ’s right shoulder.   it then appears to hover inside the net before coming in contact with the coarse netting.  the red light immediately follows,  signaling the goal.   the entire crowd jumps joyously.  they all look like bobble heads that were just shaken.  i am soon lost in a mixture of horns,  lights,  and cheering.  though when play begins,  all is silent again.  the game continues,  but nothing more occurs  that period.   two periods later,  the green light is lit recognizing the end of the game.  the one goal is left to stand alone on the scoreboard.  the crowd is overjoyed,  and all head home after the well earned victory.

title: Lifes Wonders
author: sheena
text: life.  what is life? life is a single grain of sand that is blown away by the strong wind of fate.  as if a puppet,  we go where it takes us.      knowlegde.  what is knowlegde? knowlegde is an addictive drink that the mind thirsts for.  when will this thirst be quenched? never.       love.  what is love? love is friendship.  with out friendship,  how will you love.       poems.  what are poems? poems are like petels of the flower of life.  rich in color and very,  very delicate.       song.  what is song? song is the one thing that can melt a heart of stone.  if there was no song,  how would we melt a heart.        nature.  what is nature? nature is our mother.  she pampers us with her beauty and breathtaking sites.  she also punishes us with violent earthquakes and volcanic eruptions.  when will we thank her?      blessings.  what are blessings? blessings are the good luck that can only be found in your parents hands.  with these hands,  parents lift their offspring to high heights.       language.  what is language? language is how our species communicates.  it's funny,  though,  that we all speak diversed languages when we are all breathing,   moving humans.        reading.  what is reading? reading is not a time pass,  but a window to your future.  if you don't open this window,  you will sufficate with no future.         it is now in my best hopes that now you understand how important life is.  life is full of knowlegde to obtain,  love to gain,  poems to enjoy,  song sometimes full of coy,  nature not to be missed,  blessings full of bliss,  language full of diversity,  and reading that happens not just in a college university! so be successfull in life and someday soon,  you'll be sharp as a knife.

title: Best Friends
author: shelby
text: remember when you were little and you met your first friend? well i sure do.  his name is mark,  although i don't remember his last name.  i remember when we first met.  i don't remember every detail,  but all i know was that there were new neighbors moving in a few houses down from ours and they had a boy my age named mark and then next thing you know,  we are best friends.  we did absolutely everything together.  every single day we would play together and be together. . .  we learned our abc's together,  we learned to swim together,  we learned to ride our bikes together,  we went to the same preschool so everyday we would go in the same car and we would never separate from each other.  i guess you can say we came in a package deal.  we were that way for four years until i had to move to hawaii,  but two years later we came to visit,  but he seemed more uncomfortable around me and that's when i found out we were drifting apart.     and then we moved to oregon two years ago. . . never talked to him since.  but just this summer we went to california and i asked if we could visit him.  and that's when i found out he moved to l. a. ,  my mom didn't want to tell me because she knew i would cry,  and that's exactly what i did. . . cry like a baby.  and that's were my nightmare started.  ever since i found that out,  i've had a dream were i some how found out his new address and i went to his house,  but he never remembered me.  and every time i have that dream,  i wake up crying.     if there was anyway to talk or meet him again,  then i would do it.  i would eat ten spiders if i had to.  i always wounder what he looks like now,  i don't know why,  but i'm curious.    i don't have many pictures of him left,  but every once and i while,  i look at them and remind myself who my real and true friend is.  and no one can replace him and our friendship.
